The paper discusses the use of Deep Reinforcement Learning for on-line optimization of schedules for building energy management systems. This involves the use of advanced machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the Computer Science sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of these techniques to the smart grid context, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CY (Cybersecurity). Finally, the paper also discusses the validation of the proposed approach on a large-scale database, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
